<H3> <TI>   Li Lanqing Receives U.S., SRV Visitors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Lanqing Receives U.S., SRV Visitors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0905111994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1043 GMT 9 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0905111994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 9 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li 
Lanqing met with Salim Ibrahim, vice-president of the U.S.-based 
Du Pont company, and his party here this afternoon. 
  Ibrahim, who is also chairman of the World Textile 
Association, arrived here may 7 as guest of the China National 
Textile Council. 
  Later, Vice-Premier Li met and had a friendly conversation 
with Nguyen Trong Vinh, former Vietnamese ambassador to China, 
and his group. 
  The Vietnamese guests arrived here May 7 at the invitation 
of 
the Chinese People's Institute of Foreign Affairs (CPIFA). 
President Liu Shuqing of the CPIFA today also met with them and 
hosted a dinner in their honor. 

