<H3> <TI>   Jiang Zemin Receives Foreign Participants in `China Summit' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jiang Zemin Receives Foreign Participants in `China Summit' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1005144694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1357 GMT 10 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1005144694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 10 (XINHUA) -- Chinese President Jiang 
Zemin met here this afternoon with foreign participants in the 
1994 China summit meeting, a high-profile economic forum 
scheduled to open here tomorrow. 
  The two-day meeting is to be convened by the INTERNATIONAL 
HERALD TRIBUNE (IHT) and China's State Commission for 
Restructuring the Economy with the theme of "The Chinese 
socialist market economy: cooperation with global business". 
  Malaysian Prime Minister Mohamed Mahathir, Director-General 
of the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade Peter Sutherland, 
the World Bank's Managing Director Ernest Stern, and Helmut 
Schmidt, former chancellor of the Federal Republic of Germany, 
will attend the summit meeting. 
  It marks the first time ever for China to hold such a 
high-level economic forum. 
  Present at today's meeting were IHT Publisher Richard 
McClean, Percy Barnevik, president of Asea Brown Boveri Ltd. 
(ABB), Ronald B. Woodard, president of the Boeing commercial 
airplane group, Patrick J. Ward, chairman of Caltex Petroleum 
Corporation, and Philip Tose, chairman of the Peregrine 
Investments Holdings Ltd. 
  Jiang extended a welcome to them on their participation in 
the forum and exchanged views with the guests on issues of 
strengthening international exchanges and cooperation. 
  Li Tieying, State Councillor and minister in charge of the 
State Commission for Restructuring the Economy, was also present 
at today's meeting in the Great Hall of the People. 

</TEXT>

