<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Says Jiang's ROK Visit `Just a Matter of Time' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Says Jiang's ROK Visit `Just a Matter of Time' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1005001694 Seoul YONHAP in English 0004 GMT 10 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1005001694 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 10 (YONHAP) -- Chinese President Jiang 
Zemin will pay an official visit to South Korea in the second 
quarter of this year, according to a Foreign Ministry spokesman. 
  In a meeting with South Korean correspondents here, 
Spokesman 
Chen Guosang said Monday that "the Chinese leader will 
definitely visit South Korea." 
  "A foreign visit by the top Chinese leader is customarily 
decided upon in relatively short time before the actual visit 
takes place," Chen said. "President Jiang's visit to South Korea 
is just a matter of time." 
  The spokesman thus did not rule out the possibility that 
Jiang's Seoul visit could be realized earlier than generally 
expected. 
  President Kim Yong-sam extended an invitation to Jiang to 
visit South Korea during their march summit meeting in Beijing, 
which the Chinese president accepted. 

</TEXT>

