<F P=100> Near East &amp; South Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   More on Evacuation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More on Evacuation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1005115694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1139 GMT 10 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1005115694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 10 (XINHUA) -- All the Chinese in Yemen 
are safe and sound and will leave the country very soon, a 
spokesman for the Chinese Foreign Ministry said here today. 
  In response to a question whether the Chinese in Yemen have 
been evacuated as recently serious armed conflicts have taken 
place in Yemen, the spokesman said the Chinese Government is 
very concerned about the safety of the Chinese diplomats, 
engineers and workers in Yemen, and has instructed departments 
concerned to arrange for their evacuation. 
  On May 5, armed conflicts occurred between the south and 
north sides of Yemen, with the fighting mainly concentrated in 
south part of the country. 
  Up to now, he said, all the Chinese in Yemen are safe and 
sound. 
  He said that most of the Chinese personnel working in the 
south have already been evacuated to Djibouti by sea. "The rest 
will leave very soon", he added. 
  The spokesman said that the evacuation "is conducted in a 
smooth fashion". 

</TEXT>

