<F P=106> [By reporter Wu Ping (0702 1627)] </F>
  [Text] Stockholm, 8 May (XINHUA) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman 
of the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference, this afternoon went to the Chinese 
Embassy in Sweden to call on embassy staff and meet with Chinese 
nationals and Chinese student representatives in Sweden. 
  Li Ruihuan briefed the embassy staff on the domestic 
situation. He encouraged them to work hard and make even greater 
contributions to further strengthening Sino-Swedish friendship. 
  During his meeting with Chinese nationals and student 
representatives, Li Ruihuan expressed the hope that they would 
promote the development of Sino-Swedish relations in all areas 
by making use of their intimate knowledge of both Sweden and 
China. He also expressed the hope that Chinese students would 
acquire Sweden's advanced knowledge and use it to serve their 
motherland. 
  Li Ruihuan also had a photo session with the embassy staff, 
local Chinese nationals, and Chinese student representatives. 

