BFN 

  [Text] Oslo, May 10 (XINHUA) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the 
national committee of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), arrived here this afternoon for 
a three-day official goodwill visit to Norway. 
  Norwegian acting prime minister and foreign minister, Bjorn 
Tore Godal, greeted the Chinese guest at a hotel where Li stays. 
  Upon his arrival, Li said in a written statement that he was 
expecting to exchange views on bilateral relations and 
international issues of common concern with Norwegian leaders 
during his visit to the country. 
  He also expressed the hope that his current visit would 
promote mutual understanding, cooperation and friendship between 
the China and Norway. 
  Li started visiting the Nordic nation at the invitation of 
the Norwegian Government. It is the Chinese leader's third leg 
of his current five-European-nation tour which has already taken 
him to Finland and Sweden. 

