<H3> <TI>   UK Names New Ambassador to China </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UK Names New Ambassador to China </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1005155494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1535 GMT 10 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1005155494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] London, May 10 (XINHUA) -- Britain has appointed 
veteran diplomat Len Appleyard as its next ambassador to China, 
the Foreign Office announced today. 
  Appleyard, who replaces the retiring Sir Robin McLaren, will 
take over his post in September, the Foreign Office said in a 
statement. 
  The 55-year-old Appleyard, who is a Mandarin speaker, served 
as a second secretary in the British Embassy in Beijing in the 
early 1970's. 
  He also worked as a counselor in Paris and as ambassador to 
Hungary from 1986 to 1989 before working in London as political 
director in the Foreign Office. 

</TEXT>

