<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Investment Improves Fuzhou's Urban Districts in </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Investment Improves Fuzhou's Urban Districts in </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Fujian 

<F P=102>   OW1105040694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0316 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1105040694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>
BFN 

  [Text] Fuzhou, May 11 (XINHUA) -- This capital of 
southeast China's Fujian Province has made remarkable headway in 
improving its old urban districts with overseas investment. 
  A local official said that the city government had approved 
the establishment of 310 overseas-funded companies engaged in 
real estate business by the end of last year. 
  These companies had a combined investment of 2.5 billion 
U.S. 
dollars, including contractual overseas funds totalling 2.2 
billion U.S. dollars. 
  The city has already leased out 442.3 ha [hectare] of land 
and approved 134 overseas-funded real estate projects. 
  So far, construction of projects with a total floor space of 
3.5 million sq m and accounting for 60.7 percent of the city's 
target are proceeding well and some have been completed. 
  The official attributed the progress to the city 
government's 
policy of unified planning and transforming stretches of old 
districts; and leasing the land-use rights through public 
bidding while positively improving investment conditions. 
  The city government has also simplified formalities and 
improved services for overseas business people. 

</TEXT>

