<H3> <TI>   Markets Expanding in Jiangsu's Suzhou </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Markets Expanding in Jiangsu's Suzhou </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1105080994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0642 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1105080994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nanjing, May 11 (XINHUA) -- Suzhou, an economically 
booming city in Jiangsu Province, east China, is expanding 
markets of factors of production. 
  It has 59 key markets for capital, skilled workers and 
professionals, labor, real estate, futures, technology, 
information, auctions and production equipment. 
  The labor market comprises 201 job-recommendation stations. 
These stations have helped 120,000 people find suitable jobs. 
  Some 650 technology and trading organizations at the science 
and technology market have concluded 3,652 contracts involving 
about 100 million yuan. 
  Last year saw the transactional volume on the real estate 
market amount to 218 million yuan. 
  The Suzhou office of the Jiangsu Interbank Loan Center alone 
handled 3.513 billion yuan in loans last year. 

</TEXT>

