2300 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1005233194 </F>
<F P=104>  Shanghai People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Morning News" program] </F>
  [Text] On 17 April Jiang Chunyun, member of the CPC 
Central Committee Political Bureau and secretary of the Shandong 
provincial CPC Committee, met with members of a Shanghai study 
group in Shandong led by Wang Liping, deputy secretary of the 
Shanghai municipal CPC Committee, and Vice Mayor Zhao Qizheng. 
The two sides discussed ways to further economic cooperation 
between their localities and held that Shanghai and Shandong 
will cooperate to launch a new round of south-north economic 
contacts. 
  According to JIEFANG RIBAO, the Shanghai study group was 
organized based on opinions by Wu Bangguo, member of the CPC 
Central Committee Political Bureau and secretary of the Shanghai 
municipal CPC Committee, and Mayor Huang Ju following their 
inspection of Shandong. 
  Comrade Wang Liping, deputy secretary of the Shanghai 
municipal CPC Committee, said: We are determined to come to 
Shandong to learn from its experience, and will have handsome 
rewards. After returning to Shanghai, we will earnestly study 
and materialize the Shandong experience for quick results. Vice 
Mayor Zhao Qizheng stated emphatically: The opportunity to 
develop and open up the Pudong district to the outside world 
belongs to the entire nation. It is Shanghai's responsibility to 
share this opportunity with Shandong. 

</TEXT>

