<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Municipality's Exports `Soaring' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shanghai Municipality's Exports `Soaring' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1105040594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0317 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1105040594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, May 11 (XINHUA) -- Shanghai's exports are 
soaring this year. 
  According to the latest statistics, Shanghai, China's 
largest 
economic center, exported 2.464 billion U.S. dollars-worth of 
goods in the first four months of this year, an increase of 
26.64 percent over the same period of last year. 
  A municipal foreign trade official estimated that the city's 
exports will climb to 8.5 billion U.S. dollars this year, up 
15.4 percent over 1993 and exceeding the city's annual gross 
domestic product. 
  Shanghai's key export products include ships, complete sets 
of equipment, machine tools, sewing machines, containers, 
garments, toys and shoes. 
  In addition, the city has set up 420 trading and non-trading 
enterprises in more than 60 countries and regions to promote 
sales of Shanghai-made goods. 

</TEXT>

