<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Implements Regulations for Auditors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shanghai Implements Regulations for Auditors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1105081094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0648 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1105081094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, May 11 (XINHUA) -- A professional 
auditors office regulations went into effect here yesterday. 
  The sources said the regulations contain 24 articles 
describing the legal position, business range, rights and 
responsibilities of professional auditors offices, and the 
qualifications needed by practitioners. 
  According to the regulations, auditors offices may undertake 
business from Sino-foreign joint ventures, private enterprises 
and individuals. 
  Shanghai now has 54 such offices, employing some 2,000 
professionals. They undertook 37,500 items of auditing and 
consultancy services last year, saving 236 million yuan in 
construction expenses for their customers, said the sources. 

</TEXT>

