<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Self-Employed Households Increase in Guangdong Province </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Self-Employed Households Increase in Guangdong Province </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1105015194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0134 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1105015194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, May 11 (XINHUA) -- In the first quarter 
this year, more than 22,000 new employees were hired by 
self-employed households in south China's Guangdong Province. 
  The number of registered self-employed households reached 
1.22 million with 2.24 million employees. 
  Registered funds per household in Guangdong averaged 9,170 
yuan, increasing by 5.1 percent over the average fund at the end 
of 1993. 
  With the development of the socialist market economic 
structure, governments at various levels in Guangdong have set 
great store by the growth of self-employed households. 
  The governments in Guangzhou, Zhongshan, Shaoguan, Jiangmen 
and Zhuhai cities have set preferential policies to support the 
development of this type of private economy. 
  Meanwhile, Guangdong Province has also accelerated 
construction of market places for the activities of 
self-employed households. 
  In 1993, the provinces constructed more than 400 market 
places with an area of about 2 million square meters. 
  In the first three months, the business volume of 
self-employed households in Guangdong exceeded 10 billion yuan, 
and retail sales of the households were 6.88 billion yuan, 
accounting for 17.73 percent of the total retail sales of the 
province. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

