<F P=100> West Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Ruihuan Holds Talks With Swedish Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Ruihuan Holds Talks With Swedish Prime Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1005134994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1332 GMT 10 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1005134994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Stockholm, May 10 (XINHUA) -- Visiting Chairman of 
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) Li Ruihuan held talks here today 
with Swedish Prime Minister Carl Bildt on joint efforts to 
promote bilateral relations. 
  Li Ruihuan said that China and Sweden are far away from each 
other, and have no conflict of basic interests. 
  He said that there is great potential for economic 
cooperation because the economies of the two countries are 
mutually complementary. 
  Li said China is carrying out large scale economic 
development and Swedish advanced technology and management 
experience could be very useful. 
  Bildt spoke highly of China's great achievements in economic 
reform, saying that it is important not only for China but also 
for Eastern Asia and the world economy. 
  The Swedish prime minister said that bilateral relations 
between China and Sweden have developed rapidly in recent years. 
  He also expressed Swedish support for China's reentry into 
the General Agreement on Tariff and Trade (GATT). 
  Sweden is the second stop on Li's five-European-nation tour 
which has already taken him to Finland and includes Norway, 
Denmark and Belgium. 

</TEXT>

