<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Peng Meets Entrepreneurs, Urges Economic Reform </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Peng Meets Entrepreneurs, Urges Economic Reform </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1005155194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1423 GMT 10 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1005155194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 10 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng 
today called for providing a better environment and mechanism 
for the nurturing of talents. 
  Li Peng made the remarks at a ceremony held to commend 
excellent entrepreneurs who have developed notable inventions. 
  He said that the realization of modernization in China 
depends on scientific and technological progress. 
  He said that it is significant to reward these inventive 
entrepreneurs. 
  The premier spoke highly of their efforts in transferring 
scientific and technological fruits into productive forces, 
making new products for the demands of the market and enhancing 
economic efficiency in their enterprises. 
  He called on people in various fields to set great store by 
new inventions, including large, medium and small inventions, so 
as to contribute to the prosperity of the country. 
  Other Chinese leaders Ni Zhifu, Li Peiyao, Song Jian and Luo 
Gan also attended the ceremony. 
  At the ceremony, ten inventors were granted the title of 
"excellent entrepreneur with inventive achievements" and 15 were 
honored with nomination prizes. 

</TEXT>

