<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Liu Huaqing Tours Shanghai 8-10 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Liu Huaqing Tours Shanghai 8-10 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1105062794 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0737 
GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1105062794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Chen Maodi (7115 3029 1717)] </F>
  [Text] Shanghai, 10 May (XINHUA) -- During his 8-10 May 
inspection tour of Shanghai, Liu Huaqing, member of the Standing 
Committee of the CPC Central Committee Political Bureau and vice 
chairman of the Central Military Commission [CMC], said 
emphatically: The entire party and Army, as well as people 
across the country, should subordinate themslves to the overall 
task of economic construction, further strengthen the Army's 
unity with the people and the government, and make concerted 
efforts to contribute more to the socialist modernization drive. 
  While he was in Shanghai, Comrade Liu Huaqing heard 
work-related briefings by Wu Bangguo, member of the CPC Central 
Committee Political Bureau and secretary of the Shanghai 
municipal party committee, and by Mayor Huang Ju. He also 
toured the New Pudong District. He fully affirmed Shanghai's 
achievements in economic construction. He said: The Shanghai 
municipal party committee and the municipal government have 
earnestly implemented Comrade Deng Xiaoping's theory on building 
socialism with Chinese characteristics, and they have carried 
out their work vigorously. Shanghai has undergone phenomenal 
changes, and its situation is very good. On the Yanpu bridge, 
CMC Vice Chairman Liu Huaqing joyously told Zhu Zhihao, who was 
in charge of directing the bridge's construction: The working 
class in Shanghai has rendered outstanding services and boosted 
the Chinese people's morale. 
  During his stay in Shanghai, CMC Vice Chairman Liu Huaqing 
also inspected troops on naval warships stationed in Shanghai, 
kindly encouraging naval officers and men to devote serious 
attention to acquiring modern military scientific know-how, 
undergo rigorous training, strive to improve their fighting 
capability, and further consolidate and expand their 
achievements in carrying out "double-support" work and in 
undertaking joint army-civilian efforts to promote spiritual 
civilization. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

